citations:
    citation-adwd-tyrion-iv:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "Tyrion IV"
            text_from_source: "He was on the Shy Maid, Tyrion saw, under a scratchy blanket that smelled of vinegar. The Sorrows are behind us. It was just a dream I dreamed as I was drowning … 'Lemore has been washing you with it. Some say it helps prevent the greyscale. I am inclined to doubt that, but there was no harm in trying.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Tyrion Lannister. Tyrion recovers after nearly drowning when stone men (greyscale victims) attacked the Shy Maid at the Bridge of Dream in the Sorrows. Griff pulled Tyrion from the river. Septa Lemore forced water from his lungs. Haldon uses a knife to test Tyrion's fingers and toes for greyscale numbness — the early symptoms. Unknown to Tyrion, he has contracted greyscale from contact with the stone man. The Shy Maid is now at Selhorys on the Rhoyne."
